quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  45,33,"The evil deeds they have committed will appear before them while whatever they were joking about will sweep in around them."
  45,34,"It will be said: 'Today we shall forget you just as you forgot about a Meeting on this day of yours. Your lodging will be the Fire; you have no supporters!"
  45,35,"That is because you took Allah (God)'s signs for a joke. Worldly life has lured you on." Today they will not be allowed to leave there nor will they be permitted to argue back."
  45,36,"Yet Allah (God) merits praise as Lord of Heaven and Lord of Earth; even as Lord of the Universe!"
  45,37,"He holds greatness in Heaven and Earth; He is the Powerful, the Wise!"
  46,1,"H.M."
  46,2,"The revelation of the Book [occurs] through Allah (God), the Powerful, the Wise."
  46,3,"We have only created Heaven and Earth, and whatever lies between them for the Truth and for a specific period, while those who disbelieve are dodging what they have been warned about."
  46,4,"SAY: "Have you ever seen what you appeal to instead of to Allah (God)? Show me what part of earth they have created! Have they any partnership in Heaven? Bring me a book previous to this one or any other trace of knowledge if you are so truthful.""
  46,5,"Who is further off the track than someone who appeals to something (idols) which will not respond to him until Resurrection Day, instead of to Allah (God) [Alone]? They (the idols) are oblivious [of the fact] that they are being appealed to."